<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08113e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08113e">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08113e"> 113(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Lamech&apos;s crime result / of bad books &amp; metals</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><i>Causa cur hanc historiam retulerit Moyses, forsan est ut post inventionem artium, po&euml;seos etiam inventionem referret. Forte etiam quia armorum usus cum ferri malleati inventione invectus occasionem huic homicidio dederit.</i> <br><font color="green">[The reason why Moses mentions this story, is perhaps that after the invention of the arts and skills, it also accounts for the invention of poetry. Perhaps that is also the case because the introduction of the use of weapons with the invention of wrought iron caused the opportunity for this homicide.]</font> <small> Thomas Josephus Lamy, <a name="TJLC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TJLC"><cite title="source">Commentarium in librum geneseos</cite></a> (1884) 261</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
